###Block: Uncanny Dodge and Improved Uncanny Dodge --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Use: ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Uncanny Dodge ~ Base to add the Uncanny Dodge/Improved Uncanny Dodge feature
# Add: BONUS:VAR|UncannyDodgeLevel|1 for each time the class gets either Uncanny Dodge or Improved Uncanny Dodge
# put this on class line one of any class that gets Uncanny Dodge
#	BONUS:VAR|UncannyDodgeFlankingLevel|CL|TYPE=EachClass.STACK
# Ability Name		Category of Ability		Type						Visible	Define										Description																																								Ability																											Modify VAR								Source Page
Uncanny Dodge ~ Base	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Internal				VISIBLE:NO	DEFINE:UncannyDodgeFlankingLevel|0	DEFINE:UncannyDodgeLevel|0																																										ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Uncanny Dodge|PREVAREQ:UncannyDodgeLevel,1	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Improved Uncanny Dodge|PREVARGTEQ:UncannyDodgeLevel,2
#
Uncanny Dodge		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES												DESC:You can react to danger before your senses would normally allow you to do so. You retain your Dexterity bonus to AC (If any) even if you are caught flat-footed or struck by an invisible attacker. You still lose your AC bonus if immobilized.																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.40
Improved Uncanny Dodge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES												DESC:You can no longer be flanked. This defense denies another rogue the ability to sneak attack you, unless the attacker is a rogue of at least level %1.|UncannyDodgeFlankingLevel																																							BONUS:VAR|UncannyDodgeFlankingLevel|4|TYPE=OnceOnly	SOURCEPAGE:p.40

